    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="521"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">262.11/22</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        German Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thomsen</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-02">November 2,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your note of October 21,
                        1939<note n="17" xml:id="d521fn17">Not printed.</note> in which you ask
                    whether the Government of the United States agrees to the proposal made by the
                    Government of the German Reich in your Embassy’s note of July 22, 1939 that the
                    operation of the Extradition Treaty of July 12, 1930 between the United States
                    and the German Reich shall now extend also to the territory in which the former
                    Austro-American Extradition Treaty was effective.</p>
                <p>The Government of the United States agrees to this proposal of the Government of
                    the German Reich.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
